  "text": "Chronic stress conditions during childhood can lead to depression and anxiety, as well as obesity and metabolic syndrome. [CITATION_1] In addition, children and adolescents with increased hypothalamicpituitary-adrenal axis activity have greater weight gain in adulthood. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Chronic stress causes different and permanent (systemic and testicular) changes in adulthood when applied before puberty. These rats had elevated body weights, indicating a tendency for obesity in the future.",
